'''tcpdump''' is a common [[computer network]] [[debug]]ging tool that runs under the [[command line]]. It allows the user to intercept and display [[TCP/IP]] and other packets being transmitted or received over a [[computer network|network]] to which the computer is attached. It was originally written by [[Van Jacobson]], [[Craig Leres]] and [[Steven McCanne]] who were, at the time, working in the [[Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory]] Network Research Group.
